The paper focuses on the application of deep learning to robotics, specifically in the context of object recognition and grasp planning for surface decluttering. This falls under the robotics subfield of computer science, which is cs.RO. Additionally, the paper discusses computer vision techniques for image processing and recognition (cs.CV), machine learning algorithms for deep model training (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence for decision-making and planning (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also addresses issues related to network infrastructure and communication in distributed systems, which falls under the systems subfield of computer science (cs.SY).
